The Li5.5PS4.5Cl1.5–xFx (0 < x ≤ 1.5) (denoted as LPSCl1.5–xFx) was prepared via the ball-milling and solid-state sintering reaction, in which LiF was used to replace some of the LiCl during the fabrication. Figure 1a presents the phase analysis results of annealed LPSCl1.5–xFx (x = 0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1, 1.25, 1.5). All samples predominantly exhibited an argyrodite Li6PS5Cl structure (cubic, space group \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
